```js
const sleep = (ms) => new Promise((resolve) => setTimeout(resolve, ms));

// Retry `fn` up to `n` times, waiting an exponentially growing delay between
// attempts: baseMs, baseMs*2, baseMs*4, ... The final failure is rethrown
// with no trailing sleep.
async function retry(fn, n, baseMs = 100) {
  for (let i = 0; i < n; i++) {
    try {
      return await fn();
    } catch (e) {
      if (i === n - 1) throw e;
      await sleep(baseMs * 2 ** i);   // 2**i → 1×, 2×, 4×, 8× baseMs
    }
  }
}
```

What changed versus your version: the single added line `await sleep(baseMs * 2 ** i)` inside `catch`, guarded so it runs only when another attempt will follow. Everything else (success returns immediately, last failure rethrows) is preserved.

